### listar plugins de conectores disponibles — verificar que io.debezium.connector.jdbc.JdbcSinkConnector esté presente
### si no está, la imagen de debezium debe reconstruirse (ver debezium/Dockerfile)
GET http://localhost:8083/connector-plugins

### verificar conectores registrados
GET http://localhost:8083/connectors

### PASO 1 — conector source
### Captura los cambios en la tabla operations y publica en sync.public.operations.
### Separado del conector v3: los schemas están habilitados aquí para que el JDBC Sink
### pueda inferir nombres de columnas y tipos sin un Schema Registry.
POST http://localhost:8083/connectors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "sync-source-connector",
  "config": {
    "connector.class": "io.debezium.connector.postgresql.PostgresConnector",
    "database.hostname": "postgres_db",
    "database.port": "5432",
    "database.dbname": "operations_db",
    "database.user": "postgres",
    "database.password": "postgres",
    "topic.prefix": "sync",
    "table.include.list": "public.operations",
    "plugin.name": "pgoutput",
    "slot.name": "sync_operations_slot",
    "publication.name": "sync_operations_pub",
    "snapshot.mode": "initial",
    "key.converter": "org.apache.kafka.connect.json.JsonConverter",
    "key.converter.schemas.enable": "true",
    "value.converter": "org.apache.kafka.connect.json.JsonConverter",
    "value.converter.schemas.enable": "true"
  }
}

### PASO 2 — conector sink
### Lee desde sync.public.operations y escribe en critical_db.
### Los converters deben coincidir exactamente con el source (JsonConverter + schemas.enable=true)
### para que el sink pueda deserializar el envelope de Debezium e inferir los tipos de columnas.
POST http://localhost:8083/connectors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "sync-sink-connector",
  "config": {
    "connector.class": "io.debezium.connector.jdbc.JdbcSinkConnector",
    "connection.url": "jdbc:postgresql://postgres_db:5432/critical_db",
    "connection.username": "critical_user",
    "connection.password": "sup3rS3cr3tP4ssw0rd",
    "dialect.name": "PostgreSqlDatabaseDialect",
    "topics": "sync.public.operations",
    "insert.mode": "upsert",
    "primary.key.mode": "record_key",
    "primary.key.fields": "id",
    "delete.enabled": "true",
    "table.name.format": "operations",
    "schema.evolution": "basic",
    "key.converter": "org.apache.kafka.connect.json.JsonConverter",
    "key.converter.schemas.enable": "true",
    "value.converter": "org.apache.kafka.connect.json.JsonConverter",
    "value.converter.schemas.enable": "true"
  }
}

### verificar estado del conector source — confirmar tasks[0].state = RUNNING
GET http://localhost:8083/connectors/sync-source-connector/status

### verificar estado del conector sink — confirmar tasks[0].state = RUNNING
### si tasks[0].state = FAILED, el campo trace muestra el error real
GET http://localhost:8083/connectors/sync-sink-connector/status

### reiniciar tarea del sink después de corregir el error subyacente
### usar cuando tasks[0].state = FAILED
POST http://localhost:8083/connectors/sync-sink-connector/tasks/0/restart

### reiniciar tarea del source
POST http://localhost:8083/connectors/sync-source-connector/tasks/0/restart

### eliminar ambos conectores
DELETE http://localhost:8083/connectors/sync-source-connector

###
DELETE http://localhost:8083/connectors/sync-sink-connector
